I have to vent a bit. I am very disappointed with the kill off of Joel. And I'm somebody who loved Game of Thrones, Walking Dead, the Sopranos, Breaking Bad, etc. My core issue is that there are good ways to kill off characters, and I don't feel this was one of them. Yeah yeah I get it - "oh it's crucial to tell the story!". My main issue is I watched the show for Joel. The rest of the characters, Ellie included, do not interest me. In Game of Thrones with the Ned kill off, yes, it was sad, but there was such a big cast that I connected to. In any show where you kill off a main character, the viewers are always looking to "who do I follow next". None of the characters in the Last of Us interest me enough. Why should I care about Abby? I've seen maybe 25 minutes of her. I've seen maybe 40 minutes of Tommy. It was like when they killed off Rick in the Walking Dead. Who's left? Daryll? Not enough. The Glen kill off, ok, very sad but, I cared about the rest of the people enough to continue. I watched this show for Joel, and wow omg there's going to be a vengeance arc against some random girl named Abby, couldn't care less. I get it, it was the story of the game. Well, maybe in the game Ellie was interesting enough. But this Ellie just argues with everybody and is ultra confrontational. I want to see diversity in main characters. Joel was that 100%. When he killed off the people at the hospital, he was objectively wrong, but you cheered for him anyway. I don't care enough for Ellie as a main character because she doesn't have that. So who's next to follow? Nobody. Abby doesn't interest me enough. Wow your doctor dad who I saw for 8 seconds in season 1, why should I care? Shows need to give me a reason to care. The Sopranos for example. Tony is objectively a terrible person. But you see the complexity in his character and you cheer for him. The only reason I'd cheer for Ellie is because I loved Joel. Not because I like Ellie. I heard Ellie's character is more complex in the games and perhaps this kill off creates a beautiful vengeance arc in the game. But I'm not seeing it in the show. Very disappointed because I was really enjoying the Last of Us and figured it may reach the standard of Sopranos, Breaking Bad, etc. But I guess not.
